---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = 'Token Budget';
const subtitle = 'The reader is finite. Slide the graph size; watch the paste break.';
---
<Base title={title} description={subtitle}>
  <article class="etude">
    <p class="essay-kicker">Etude · Know Thyself, Part II</p>
    <h1>{title}</h1>
    <p class="essay-sub">{subtitle}</p>
    <div class="essay-meta">
      <a href="/essays/know-thyself-search/">← back to essay</a>
    </div>
    <hr />

    <p>A graph that fit cleanly into the model's context at three hundred nodes will fail at three thousand. The corpus didn't get worse. The reader has a bounded window, and once the paste exceeds it, recall and inference both degrade — gradually, then sharply.</p>

    <p>Move the slider. Watch what the model says about Alex's graph as the context fills.</p>

    <div class="controls">
      <label class="slider-label" for="size">Graph size</label>
      <input id="size" type="range" min="100" max="5000" step="50" value="300" />
      <div class="readout" id="readout">Nodes: 300 | Tokens: ~12,600 | Context fill: 16%</div>
      <div class="presets">
        <button type="button" class="preset" data-target="300">300 nodes (works fine)</button>
        <button type="button" class="preset" data-target="1200">1,200 nodes (friction)</button>
        <button type="button" class="preset" data-target="3000">3,000 nodes (it stops)</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="window-wrap">
      <div class="window-bar"><div class="window-fill" id="fill"></div></div>
      <div class="window-warn" id="warn" aria-live="polite"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="chat" id="chat">
      <div class="msg msg-user">here's my graph: <span class="paste" id="paste">[300 nodes pasted]</span> — what's true about Alex?</div>
      <div class="msg msg-bot" id="bot">I see Alex is connected to her sister via a recurring Sunday-call pattern, and her job-search thread links back to a pattern node about deferring decisions when uncertain. Want me to trace either?</div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="chart-h">Answer specificity vs context fill</h3>
    <div class="chart">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 400 140" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true">
        <line x1="40" y1="110" x2="390" y2="110" stroke="currentColor" stroke-opacity="0.25" />
        <line x1="40" y1="110" x2="40" y2="20" stroke="currentColor" stroke-opacity="0.25" />
        <text x="40" y="128" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.6">0%</text>
        <text x="195" y="128" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.6">50%</text>
        <text x="370" y="128" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.6">100%</text>
        <text x="6" y="28" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.6">high</text>
        <text x="6" y="112" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.6">low</text>
        <path id="curve" d="" fill="none" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="2" />
        <circle id="dot" cx="0" cy="0" r="4" fill="var(--accent)" />
      </svg>
    </div>

    <hr />

    <p>The graph is correct. The reader is finite. Retrieval is the bridge. The bound is about the reader, not the corpus — which is why the same shape that matters for Exa over the open web matters for one person's graph at three hundred nodes.</p>

    <p class="fineprint">Long-context degradation is documented across the literature: needle-in-haystack precision drops sharply past mid-window, and recall on multi-hop queries decays well before the model refuses outright. The exact thresholds vary by model; the curve shape doesn't.</p>
  </article>
</Base>

<script is:inline>
  const slider = document.getElementById('size');
  const readout = document.getElementById('readout');
  const fill = document.getElementById('fill');
  const warn = document.getElementById('warn');
  const bot = document.getElementById('bot');
  const paste = document.getElementById('paste');
  const curve = document.getElementById('curve');
  const dot = document.getElementById('dot');

  // Approx 42 tokens/node and 80k-token effective window for the demo.
  const TOK_PER_NODE = 42;
  const WINDOW_TOK = 80000;

  const responses = [
    { max: 0.30, text: "I see Alex is connected to her sister via a recurring Sunday-call pattern, and her job-search thread links back to a pattern node about deferring decisions when uncertain. Want me to trace either?" },
    { max: 0.55, text: "Alex's graph shows a connection between her sister and a Sunday routine, and a separate cluster around job-search uncertainty. The link between those two clusters is faint." },
    { max: 0.75, text: "There's a connection between Alex and a sibling, and another between Alex and a job-related thread. Some uncertainty patterns appear." },
    { max: 0.92, text: "There appears to be some relevant content about Alex in the graph, including family and career nodes." },
    { max: 1.00, text: "I'm unable to process this much context effectively. Please reduce the input size or summarize." }
  ];

  function pickResponse(frac) {
    for (const r of responses) if (frac <= r.max) return r.text;
    return responses[responses.length - 1].text;
  }

  // Specificity curve: ~1 until 0.5, drops via sigmoid past 0.7, floors near 1.
  function specificity(frac) {
    if (frac < 0.5) return 1 - frac * 0.1;
    const k = 14;
    const x0 = 0.78;
    return Math.max(0.05, 1 - 1 / (1 + Math.exp(-k * (frac - x0))) * 0.95);
  }

  function buildCurvePath() {
    const pts = [];
    for (let i = 0; i <= 100; i++) {
      const f = i / 100;
      const x = 40 + f * 350;
      const y = 110 - specificity(f) * 90;
      pts.push((i === 0 ? 'M' : 'L') + x.toFixed(1) + ',' + y.toFixed(1));
    }
    curve.setAttribute('d', pts.join(' '));
  }
  buildCurvePath();

  function fmt(n) { return n.toLocaleString('en-US'); }

  function update(nodes, animateBar) {
    const tokens = Math.round(nodes * TOK_PER_NODE);
    const frac = Math.min(1, tokens / WINDOW_TOK);
    const pct = Math.round(frac * 100);

    readout.textContent = `Nodes: ${fmt(nodes)} | Tokens: ~${fmt(tokens)} | Context fill: ${pct}%`;
    paste.textContent = `[${fmt(nodes)} nodes pasted]`;
    fill.style.width = (frac * 100).toFixed(1) + '%';

    let tier = 'ok';
    if (frac > 0.95) tier = 'red';
    else if (frac > 0.70) tier = 'amber';
    fill.dataset.tier = tier;

    if (tier === 'red') warn.innerHTML = '<span class="warn-icon">⚠</span> inference quality degrading';
    else if (tier === 'amber') warn.innerHTML = '<span class="warn-icon warn-amber">●</span> approaching window limit';
    else warn.textContent = '';

    bot.dataset.tier = tier;
    bot.textContent = pickResponse(frac);

    const cx = 40 + frac * 350;
    const cy = 110 - specificity(frac) * 90;
    dot.setAttribute('cx', cx.toFixed(1));
    dot.setAttribute('cy', cy.toFixed(1));
  }

  slider.addEventListener('input', e => update(parseInt(e.target.value, 10), false));

  document.querySelectorAll('.preset').forEach(btn => {
    btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const target = parseInt(btn.dataset.target, 10);
      const start = parseInt(slider.value, 10);
      const t0 = performance.now();
      const dur = 600;
      function step(now) {
        const k = Math.min(1, (now - t0) / dur);
        const eased = 1 - Math.pow(1 - k, 3);
        const v = Math.round(start + (target - start) * eased);
        slider.value = v;
        update(v, true);
        if (k < 1) requestAnimationFrame(step);
      }
      requestAnimationFrame(step);
    });
  });

  update(parseInt(slider.value, 10), false);
</script>

<style>
  .etude { max-width: 38rem; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.25rem 4rem; }
  .etude h1 { font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 2rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem; }
  .essay-sub { font-style: italic; color: var(--muted); margin: 0 0 1rem; }

  .controls {
    margin: 1.5rem 0 1rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.15rem;
    background: var(--bg-soft, rgba(0,0,0,0.03));
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .slider-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  #size {
    width: 100%;
    accent-color: var(--accent);
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  .readout {
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0.6rem 0 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }
  .presets {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .preset {
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.7rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
    border-radius: 3px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 120ms;
  }
  .preset:hover { background: rgba(138, 52, 32, 0.08); }

  .window-wrap { margin: 0.4rem 0 1.5rem; }
  .window-bar {
    height: 18px;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    border-radius: 3px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .window-fill {
    height: 100%;
    width: 16%;
    background: var(--accent);
    transition: width 220ms cubic-bezier(.2,.8,.2,1), background-color 240ms;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .window-fill[data-tier="amber"] { background: #c98a1a; }
  .window-fill[data-tier="red"] { background: #b53826; }
  .window-warn {
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    min-height: 1.1rem;
  }
  .warn-icon { color: #b53826; font-weight: bold; margin-right: 0.25rem; }
  .warn-icon.warn-amber { color: #c98a1a; }

  .chat {
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
    padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.025);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 2px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .msg { margin: 0.45rem 0; }
  .msg-user { color: var(--muted); }
  .msg-user .paste {
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    padding: 0.05rem 0.35rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .msg-bot {
    color: var(--ink);
    transition: opacity 220ms, color 220ms;
  }
  .msg-bot[data-tier="amber"] { color: #8a6a2a; }
  .msg-bot[data-tier="red"] { color: #8a3a30; opacity: 0.85; }

  .chart-h {
    font-family: 'Georgia', serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 1.4rem 0 0.4rem;
    font-weight: normal;
  }
  .chart {
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.2rem;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.02);
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .chart svg { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; color: var(--ink); }

  .fineprint { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.88rem; line-height: 1.55; }
</style>
